modules.description: Handles video playback in Cordova applications by providing methods to initialize, control, and terminate video sessions. Operates with video URLs, playback states, and device-specific configurations. Used to integrate native video playback capabilities into hybrid mobile apps, ensuring smooth user interaction with video content.

Creates and manages video playback with customizable volume and scaling settings. Operates on string video paths, callback functions, and an opaque options structure. Used to initialize playback, handle completion or error events, and terminate video sessions.
